Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of belief networks in AI and the development of efficient algorithms for probabilistic inference. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the implementation of methods for computing uncertainty in inferred probabilities, which could fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of Monte Carlo Integration Method suggests a focus on Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the discussion of reporting the range of possible error in inferred probabilities suggests a focus on Software Engineering (cs.SE).
